      • kHighGoalSpeed

        public static final double kHighGoalSpeed
        (Warning: arbritrary number) Speed for shooting to the high goal in "m/s". Note on the shooter itself, this is very janky. Supposedly the characterization and math that I did should in theory be in meter's per second but the actual speed that's output when we use the PID control loop ends up looking... not that way. They're numbers, that's for sure.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • kHighGoalThresh

        public static final double kHighGoalThresh
        Threshold speed for when the indexer should start moving the balls to the shooter. Once again, this is in "m/s" aka not actually m/s.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • kLowGoalSpeed

        public static final double kLowGoalSpeed

      • kFrontShooterMotorInverted

        public static final boolean kFrontShooterMotorInverted
